************  Kubernetes Commands-Yop Node and Pod *******************

1. kubectl get pods --all-namespaces
- retriev all pods from all the namespaces kubesystem namespaces, fluentd, kube-dns, kube-proxy, metric-server...K8S CONTROL PLANE 

2. KUBECTL GET PODS --ALL-NAMESPACES -L APP=HELLOWORLD-REST-API

3. kubectl get services --all-namespaces

4. kubectl get services --all-namespaces --sort-by=.spec.type

5. kubectl get services --all-namespaces --sort-by=.metadata.name

6. kubectl cluster-info
    * Kubernetes master is running at .....
    * GLBCDefaultBackend is running at
    * Heapster is running at ....
    * KubeDNS is running at ....
    * 
